103. Create a very simple pageview counter by using â€˜issetâ€™ to check if the pageview variable has
already been created.

ANSWER
<?php
// Start the session
session_start();

// Check if the pageview counter is set
if (!isset($_SESSION['pageviews'])) {
    $_SESSION['pageviews'] = 1; // First visit
} else {
    $_SESSION['pageviews']++; // Increment on each visit
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Simple Pageview Counter</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h2>ðŸ“Š Pageview Counter</h2>

    <p>You have visited this page <strong><?php echo $_SESSION['pageviews']; ?></strong> times during this session.</p>

    <form method="post">
        <button type="submit">Refresh Page</button>
    </form>

</body>
</html>

OUTPUT
Pageview Counter
You have visited this page 1 times during this session.
3Refresh Page
